    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="243"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20437/83.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Does your cable May 11 mean contracts will be filled at old syndicate prices?
                    American contractors state they have information that potash bill passed
                    Reichstag under misapprehension regarding views of this Government, and that if
                    position of this Government is understood, law will not be enforced. If facts
                    are as represented you will see to it that the position of this Government, as
                    set forth in the department’s cable of May 4, is thoroughly understood by the
                    German Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
